  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "ANDREW LASKA",
    "text": "During the war, I was-- my parents came from Czechoslovakia, and they were put to-- into jail. My father stayed in jail for over 3 1/2 years. I was 12 years old, when me and my brother-- when we were put into jail first. And then we were sent into a coal mine. And then I escaped from there and joined the resistance, where I was wounded twice. Survived the war and then left for the United States and Mexico, where my father was ambassador of Czechoslovakia. Eventually, I ended up at the University of Chicago, where I met Vera.",
